        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-03T18:52:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "will it be aligned enough? some opengl drivers use sse instruction to read/write data, and passing char array as float* could kill it\nalignas(double) ?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 166,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 166,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "e610851e414973d83d37418bfc41bc3a63dc2f8d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "99f28dd6_3090e713",
        "filename": "android/android-emugl/host/libs/Translator/GLES_V2/ProgramData.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 166,
      "author": {
        "id": 1129273
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-03T23:43:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "FLOAT MAT4x4 takes 64 bytes. 256 bytes here should accommodate the aligned data.",
      "parentUuid": "d4d8605c_f81dd613",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 166,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 166,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "e610851e414973d83d37418bfc41bc3a63dc2f8d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1b1e32ec_60cc24bd",
        "filename": "android/android-emugl/host/libs/Translator/GLES_V2/ProgramData.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 166,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-04T00:33:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I care more about the memory alignment of the |val|, not its size. If you pass |val| to any gl function it could crash if |val| is not aligned enough. And char type doesn\u0027t actually have any alignment requirements on itself, so it all falls back to default per-platform stack alignment. I\u0027s prefer to have explicit http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/alignas operator here to make sure drivers don\u0027t crash - e.g. take a look at GenericInputBuffer class in android/android-emugl/shared/OpenglCodecCommon/ProtocolUtils.h, it exists exactly for the same purpose",
      "parentUuid": "99f28dd6_3090e713",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 166,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 166,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "e610851e414973d83d37418bfc41bc3a63dc2f8d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
